'''Projekt: Community''' (also '''PJKT''', or '''PJKT:COM''') is a community-run [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]] virtual events organization. Since 2023 it has run a year-round calendar of conventions and seasonal activities that bring VRChat groups together in dedicated event worlds—typically through staffed booths, scheduled programming, and collaborations with world creators.<ref name="legends-wiki">[https://vrchat-legends.fandom.com/wiki/Projekt:_Community "Projekt: Community"] on ''VRChat Legends Wiki''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="ffvd-pjktfest">[https://www.ffvdgames.com/2025/06/26/im-going-to-be-at-pjktfest-2025/ "I'm Going To Be At PJKT:FEST 2025!"] on ''Flippin' Fun Video Games'' (blog). Dated June 26, 2025. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Several PJKT-branded events have been featured in VRChat's client and on its official social channels.<ref name="bsky-graffiti-2025">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com "Happy Easter, everyone! Check out the Graffiti Grab 'Easter Egg Hunt' world row on VRChat, now live until April 27! Hosted by @projektcommunity.com"] on ''Bluesky'' (@vrchat.com). Dated April 22, 2025. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="bsky-pjkt-fang-2026">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com "Winter time Blues got you down? Get excited for PJKT Fang! Lots of Events, Meetups, Panels and Live Music! Hope to see you there February 20th-23rd! #PJKTFang #VRChat"] on ''Bluesky'' (@vrchat.com). Dated February 17, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

==Overview==

Projekt: Community was founded in January 2023.<ref name="discord-pjkt">[https://discord.do/projekt-community "Projekt: Community"] on ''Discord.Do'' (Discord server listing; created January 9, 2023). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Publicity for its first festival described the organization as having grown out of former staff of VRCon, an earlier community-driven VR convention.<ref name="fa-2023-promo">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/52815205/ "PJKTCOM 2023 - Projekt Community Festival Promo 1"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity'' (posted June 2023; describes Projekt Community as "born out of the reform staff of VRCon"). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

Rather than operating a single annual show, PJKT maintains a seasonal circuit: a large summer festival, a winter convention, an Easter-period world hunt, a film festival, and a horror convention.<ref name="legends-wiki"/> Across those formats, the common pattern is to host other VRChat communities—content creators, roleplaying groups, social clubs, and creative projects—inside shared event spaces where they can run booths, panels, meetups, and entertainment.<ref name="fa-2023-promo"/><ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/>

The organization's VRChat group shortname is '''PJKT.3741'''. Many event instances are set to Groups-Public or above, so membership in that group is required to join.<ref name="fa-comops">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/64030315/ "PJKT Fang 2026 - Comrades And Ops Games 2"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (ChevronTheWolf). Posted February 15, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Attendance is free; participants need a VRChat account, and often group membership.<ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/>

==Events==

===PJKT Fest===

[[Community:PJKT_Fest|PJKT Fest]] (also called Projekt Fest or Projekt Community Festival) is the organization's flagship summer convention and has been held each year since 2023.<ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/> Editions have ranged from multi-day to roughly week-long runs, usually in June or early July, inside a dedicated festival world.<ref name="fa-2024-poster">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/57219284/ "PJKT: Festival 2024 - Promo Poster"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity'' (posted 2024; includes event dates, participating community list, and world link). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/>

The festival is built around staffed community booths and a changing daily program. Past programming has included panels and activities on topics such as sign language, improv, and virtual fitness, alongside live music and showcases of VRChat creative work.<ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/><ref name="fa-2024-poster"/> Participating groups have spanned gamers, roleplayers, improv troupes, social communities, avatar combat groups, and larger networks such as the Furry Events Community and ProtoFox Network.<ref name="fa-2024-poster"/> The 2024 edition also included a collaboration with [[wikipedia:Virtual Market (event)|Virtual Market]] (VKET).<ref name="fa-2024-vket">[https://furaffinity.net/view/57373666/ "PJKT: Fest 2024 - VKET Meet"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

===PJKT Fang===

[[Community:PJKT_Fang|PJKT Fang]] is PJKT's winter convention. The 2026 edition ran from February 20 to 23 and was promoted by VRChat on Bluesky as featuring events, meetups, panels, and live music.<ref name="bsky-pjkt-fang-2026"/> Like Fest, it uses a shared convention world where other communities set up booths—for example gaming sessions and cross-promotion for separate conventions.<ref name="fa-comops"/><ref name="lilithebowman-fang">[https://www.lilithebowman.com/blog/2026/02/ "PJKT Fang Booth Meet" and "PJKT FANG is Coming Soon!"] on ''Lilithe Bowman'' (blog). February 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

===Graffiti Grab===

[[Community:Graffiti_Grab|Graffiti Grab]] is PJKT's recurring Easter-season egg hunt. Instead of a single convention floor, it spreads across many VRChat worlds: builders hide eggs for players to find during the holiday period.<ref name="legends-wiki"/> VRChat has featured the event with curated client world rows and hub-world announcements, naming Projekt Community as host.<ref name="bsky-graffiti-2025"/><ref name="bsky-graffiti-2026">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com "Graffiti Grab is Back! Explore Worlds, Gather Eggs, and check out the New Graffiti Grab Hub! Join us for this year's easter egg hunt adventures!"] on ''Bluesky'' (@vrchat.com). Dated April 4, 2026. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref> Some editions have added collectible "spreggs" and prize raffles alongside the open hunt.<ref name="fa-graffiti-2024">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/56170428/ "PJKTCOM Graffiti Grab - Egg Hunters"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (event dates, links, and submission form in description). Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref>

===PJKT Lenz===

[[Community:PJKT_Lenz|PJKT Lenz]] (Projekt: Lenz) is PJKT's community film festival, showcasing submitted short films and filmmaking-focused programming.<ref name="legends-wiki"/> The documented 2023 edition ran from September 29 to October 1 in a festival world by Pesky12.<ref name="fa-lenz-promo">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/53925448/ "PJKT Lenz 2023 - Promo Poster"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref> Film-festival submissions have also been accepted alongside booth and event-host applications in past Fest sign-up periods.<ref name="fa-2024-signups">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/56443199/ "Projekt: Community Festival 2024 - Sign-Ups Open!"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (community-uploaded event publicity; includes historical dates and links). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

===PJKT HorrorCon===

[[Community:PJKT_HorrorCon|PJKT HorrorCon]] is a horror-themed convention run in collaboration with HorrorConVR.<ref name="legends-wiki"/> Documented editions include October 26-27, 2024, and a 2025 run that overlapped [[Community:Group_Fair|Group Fair]] programming under PJKT.3741; a further edition has been announced for October 2026.<ref name="fa-horror-2024">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/59330477/ "HorrorCon 2024 - Your Questions?"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref><ref name="pjkt-faq">[https://www.projektcommunity.com/faq "FAQ"] on ''Projekt: Community'' (site banner: "PJKT:HORRORCON IS COMING — October 2026"). Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref>

==Format and media==

Major PJKT conventions share a booth-and-programming model: other VRChat communities apply in advance, staff a presence in the event world, and contribute to a published schedule.<ref name="fa-2024-signups"/><ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/> Livestreams of festival programming are typically carried on Projekt Community's Twitch channel, with recordings posted afterward to its YouTube channel.<ref name="ffvd-pjktfest"/>

==Recognition==

In 2024, Projekt Community won a Gold Telly Award in the People's Telly category for Immersive and Mixed Reality for its ''Projekt: Festival 2023 Recap'' video.<ref name="telly-award">[https://www.tellyawards.com/winners/2024/peoples-telly/general-immersive-mixed-reality/projekt-festival-2023/307520/ "People's Telly Gold Winner: Immersive & Mixed Reality — Projekt Festival 2023"] on ''Telly Awards''. 2024 Winners. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="fa-telly">[https://furaffinity.net/view/56754904/ "PJKTCOM - A Special Announcement: Telly Awards"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (ChevronTheWolf). Posted May 21, 2024. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> The organization was also a finalist for the "Virtual Experience" award at the [[Community:VR_Community_Awards|VR Community Awards]] 2024.<ref name="vrca-past">[https://vrcommunityawards.com/past-winners "Past Winners"] on ''VR Community Awards''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

==Participation==

Booth, programming, and related applications for major events are published on the organization's website and linked social channels ahead of each run.<ref name="fa-2024-signups"/> In previous years, applications covered booth representatives, event hosts, and film festival submissions.<ref name="fa-2024-signups"/> Requirements and deadlines vary by event and year.

